# On the source machine:\npg_dump -U username -Fc dbname | gzip | ssh user@remote_host "cat > /path/to/backup/dbname.tar.gz"\n\n# Explanation:\n# pg_dump -U username -Fc dbname: Dumps the database named 'dbname' for the specified 'username' in a custom format (-Fc).\n# gzip: Compresses the output of pg_dump.\n# ssh user@remote_host "cat > /path/to/backup/dbname.tar.gz": Securely copies the compressed data to the remote host and saves it as dbname.tar.gz.